
[1]termination

   TERMINA'TION, n. The act of limiting or setting bounds; the act of
   ending or concluding.

   1. Bound; limit in space or extent; as the termination of a line.

   2. End in time or existence; as the termination of the year or of life;
   the termination of happiness.

   3. In grammar, the end or ending of a word; the syllable or letter that
   ends a word. Words have different terminations to express number, time
   and sex.

   4. End; conclusion; result.

   5. Last purpose.

   6. Word; term. [Not in use.]
